        "Episode of Series \"Horizon\". An investigation of the causes of the dramatic increase in fire-incidence figures in Britain. Demonstrates some of the new and unexpected fire hazards produced by our consumer society - new fabrics, high rise buildings and shopping precincts. Looks at research into fire prevention, and tests the public's ability to use fire extinguishers."
